parameters:
\SM[tremble]\SE[102]Ugh... It's cold... But warm...
\SE[51]But, it's cold... Warm...

\SE[52]Make sure you don't catch a cold, okay...?
\!\SE[1]Come on, you can snuggle a little closer.

\SE[2]About the document... Can I ask you about it soon?
\SE[3]Did you go all the way there for that?

\SE[50]Well... I've been helped by you guys too. I have an
obligation to explain, right? \SE[3]...Cat. Please.

\SE[4]I think you've seen it a few times too... The mineral
that serves as the energy source when using magic.
\SE[3]Strictly speaking, it's not exactly that, but just
keep that in mind.

\SE[2]So it's been declining for the past 10 years.
\!\SE[3]Oh... It's been rapidly recovering for about 2 years
now...?

\SE[2]I see. The Nileun Mine, which used to be a major
source, has been depleting... \SE[3]So three years ago, we
succeeded in new development...

\SE[3]Come to think of it, we didn't really study geography
much at school. Looking at it like this...

\SE[2]So... This is the data for the additional mining area.
\SE[57].........I see, it's just as I thought.

\SE[2]First of all... The new development mine is
originally... \SE[3]Outside the territory of Cordain... And
also...

\SE[4]The places marked with a \SE[3]symbol... Are there no
conflicts or looting happening there...?

\SE[2]That is not only a blueprint for new development, but
also a plan for conflict.

\SE[2]... Well, that's true. If we can't meet the demand
with our own production, then we should get it from
elsewhere. \SE[3] We have the national power, so starting a
fight is the best option.

\SE[51]On the way to the prison... There was a section for
political prisoners, right? \SE\SE[3]Those are the
politicians from the conservative faction who opposed
looting. They're being thrown in there with charges that
seem fitting. \SE[3]... Just like what happened to you.

\SE[4]But... I've never heard that Cordain was doing such a
thing... \SE[3]I was in the borderlands, so I didn't know...
right?

\SE[4]If we do it openly, we won't be able to avoid
criticism from neighboring countries. \!\SE[3]That's why
we're conducting proxy wars skillfully.

\SE[2]We'll have an external organization take over the
territory... \!\SE[3]And then Cordain will seize the
territory again under the pretext of suppression.

\SE[4]By maintaining face-to-face contact, we assert our
ownership of the land... You can't refuse, can you?
\SE[52]After all, we've given you peace. \SE[3]That's the
least you can do.

\SE[5]But why are you collecting so much of that... 'Rare
Earth'...? \!\SE[3]

\SE[2]As individuals, we don't rely on Rare Earth that much.
\!\SE[3]But when it comes to the country as a whole, it's a
different story...

\SE[76]Cordain's national power has been growing
remarkably... \!\SE[3]But it is completely dependent on
magic. \.If that's the case, the consumption of Rare Earth
will also become significantly higher.

\SE[2]By colluding with such a country, there are more
benefits to be gained...
\SE[33] Magic Academy... That's what it is, huh...

\SE[3]I see... \SE[1]We didn't talk much about the academy,
so when we get back, I'll tell you all about it.

\SE[2]...The next thing is the future plan document. Well,
this is the main topic though.

\SE[2]That's the best excavation site around here. \SE[3]The
Mottrell Mine within the Ulyssean territory...
\SE[5]Mottrell Mine... The place where we saved Rebecca...?

\SE[4]The main producing mines we currently have are small
to medium-sized. \!\SE[3]Probably... They will likely be
depleted in about three years.

\SE[2]... If that's the case, we have no choice but to take
it from Ulyssean with the Mottrell Mine.

\SE[75]... That country is just going through the motions.
In order to maintain growth, they have no choice but to
destroy everything around them. \SE[3] There is no other way
but to choose the means to achieve that.

\SE[2]I only put on such a poor performance just to show you
this. \SE[74]The White Mage we fought earlier... I was the
only one who found them suspicious.
\SE[75]I'm sorry for involving both of you...

\SE[76]Well... I am a fallen noble, after all.
\!\SE[51]Rather than rebuilding my family over there, I
decided to fight against those I dislike. That's all.

\SE[2]I'm saying this fully aware of how reckless it is.
\!\SE[3]...I hope you understand what I'm trying to say.

\SE[33]Please give me a little time. It's not just my
problem alone...

\SE[2]... Yes, of course. I have no intention of rushing for
an answer.

\SE[2]But... I hate to say it, but... Do we really need to
do something so dangerous? \SE[3]If we know that a war is
going to happen, why don't we all just run away together?
\SE[2]I was hesitant about whether or not to say this...

\SE[3]Vita, I also investigated about you. \!\SE[82]You're
from the Hajikko Village, right?

\SE[74]Rare Earth, you see. \SE[3]It requires a process
called refining. \SE[3]...It's necessary to make it in a
higher state of purity.

\SE[74]I'm having someone from a remote village who knows
nothing about it do it for a cheap price....

\SE[2]When you perform refining, there is absolutely... a
dangerous substance that is produced. \SE[51]Just a slight
touch from a human... it can become irreparable...

\SE[74]Did you... see it in the village? \!Their entire body
melted and turned into jelly-like substance \!They gradually
lost lung function and died from suffocation \!\SE[75]People
who experienced severe headaches and gradually lost their
ability to speak...

\SE[56]...... They were all there. \SE[57] My father... my
mother... Aisha too...

\SE[76]There is still no technology in this world to control
this substance. \!\SE[75]It is too dangerous to refine it in
our own country...

\SE[67]... I'm sorry. \SE[74] You seemed intelligent, so I
may have talked a bit too much...

\SE[2]Lunaroa. \I haven't told Laura yet...\.Right?
\!\SE[74]...From the looks of it.

\SE[92]Could it be... that Hatayaki Village... \SE[93]My
father... and my mother... \SE[53]were killed by Codain...
\SE[51]is that what happened...?

\SE[74]There was a small mountain near the village, right?
\.That area is still undeveloped.... \!\SE[51]It is highly
estimated that Rare Earth can be mined there.

\SE[85]I thought it was a difficult story. But somehow, I
understood it halfway through. \SE[51]...I understand
everything correctly. Although I'm not confident.

\SE[52]I'm sorry... If only I were stronger... \SE[38]The
people in the village... Your parents... They could have
been saved for sure...

\SE[47]The Principal with the soldiers stopped me because
they knew where I came from, the Academy. \!\SE[48]

\SE[37]By the time I finally arrived at the village... so
many people had already died...

\SE[95]No way... Lunaroa... \SE[51]It's not your fault at
all...

\SE[74]Let's rest for today... \.Because we'll be crossing
the border in the morning.... \!\SE[51]
